Dipsy 4/28/2024 7:19 PM
My small cottage rests on a hill in the country side. It is a particularly large hill that overlooks the sea of fields. I have a perfect view of these fields. It can make my day just stopping to look out at the window overseeing this beautiful sight. The sun feeds the corn and gives them life. The rain also keeps the corn alive, and assists me in sleeping. Nearby my house is a telephone pole, and is basically my gate to the outside world whenever I'm not on a business trip or out to see family. But that's in the day. At night, it's a different story. I usually cannot see much, but the dark brown sky gives me a foreboding vibe. Unless it is raining, I keep the curtains closed. I occasionally get wildlife that lurks in the corn searching for food. I've settled up little batches of seeds and meat to drive these critters away, and it usually does the job. There are also scarecrows for the birds. But... The other night.... Something was off. I went for a walk in the corn, when I noticed that it seems they had been ran over, like something big had marched through the fields, causing them to stoop to the ground. But that wasn't the most alarming thing. One of the scarecrows I had crafted, had been decapitated by ripping force. It was a good 8 feet into the air, and it took me an impeccable amount of effort to set the scarecrows up. And no animal that visits the cornfield is big enough to reach the head of the scarecrow. The way the head was removed suggests it was the work of a person. But that's not possible, as the nearest neighbour is half a mile away from the edge of the field. Last night....something happened. I was in my study, writing the article for the next paper I had been assigned to write. That's when I heard a screech from outside my cottage. It's not unusual to hear noises like this off in the fields at night, it would usually be coyotes and similar animals. But something about this felt off. So I went to the window. At least 250 meters away from my cottage, off in the distant fields, was an unnaturally tall silhouette of a male figure, reaching up to at least 10 feet. He strided through the corn with a horrifying speed, undoubtedly headed straight for my sanctuary. I was prompted to run straight to my phone, where I dialled police. I told them about my ordeal, when the call suddenly ended and the phone began to buzz. The phone lines must've been cut from the telephone pole that was nearby my house. I ran to grab a knife, selecting a huge blade from the catalogue of utensils, when the door began to bang. On the other side came graspy groaning. I quickly ran upstairs to my bedroom in search of a hiding place when i looked to my window. That thing was peering at me through the window, holding the carcass of a raccoon. But, we were on the second floor. The disfigured creature smiled at me, before beginning to write something on the window with the blood of the raccoon. "Did you lock your backdoor?" As soon as I registered this message, I heard a loud smash coming from the backdoor, and what followed was heavy footsteps coming up the stairs to my room alongside manic screeching.

I have no idea how the fire started. All I remember was smelling smoke from the other room. I live in a 3 room apartment. It had a main lobby with a living room, and then a hallway which held the bedroom, kitchen, and bathroom. So after getting out of my room and going into the kitchen, I saw the fire emanating from the oven. Grabbing a towel, I approached the onslaught, only for it to explode in my face, knocking me back and engulfing half the room in flames. It was too smoky to make sense of the situation, but I felt burns across my upper torso. I quickly got up, suffering a headache after walking myself into a wall. I got up and saw the open door through all the fog caused by the fire, and I leapt through. Iwas on the floor. The fire was beginning to spread beyond the kitchen now. The flames ate away at me. My life flashed. My little brothers birthday was tomorrow. My parents anniversary was next month. Christmas was nearing. No. I won't let the fire get me. Getting up, I felt much more lighter, and the burns began to ease down. I ran full speed towards the front door, closing my eyes as I leapt towards it. I landed in the concrete floor outside. I didn't feel the door. It was still closed, yet I was outside. Getting back up, the bystanders and firefighters surrounding my house didn't seem to acknowledge me. Instead, they were fixated on my now ruined house. I couldn't even sit on a bench without somehow hitting the grass ground beneath. I get back up, wandering backwards, somehow phasing through a lamppost. This can't be right. I look at my clothes. They... Aren't charred and burnt, but back there I was on fire. I see that the firefighters had now kicked open my front door, only to see my living room decimated with fire. But... In the midst of it all.... A body lay. Still burning. CREDIT: @Dipsy
